Turkish Opposition Will Spend $7 Billion on Poor, Haberturk Says

-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 
2011-02-17T06:55:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/turkish-opposition-will-spend-7-billion-on-poor-haberturk-says.html
  Turkey ’s main opposition party will
spend 1.7 percent of the budget, or $7 billion, on an aid
package for the poor, increasing the spending from $2.5 billion
currently should it win a June general election, Haberturk
reported.  The financial aid will include help with childrens’ school
fees and payments to women, the newspaper said citing Republican
People’s Party leader  Kemal Kilicdaroglu .   Payments to families will be a minimum of 600 liras ($380)
per month to as much as 1,250 liras ($700) per month for a
family with seven children, according to Haberturk.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
